            London's 'friendliest bus driver' gets his own film
            Passengers on the 214 through Camden know their driver well. But now Ahmed Serhani's happy-go-lucky attitude has landed him a film role.The six minute film, called 'Ahmed Serhani, A portrait', will be premiered at the London Transport Museum next year.Mr Serhani said: "It's in my nature anyway to talk to people, approach them and as a bus driver that's even more important."
                
                        30 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
